stylometry: The factors and trade offs one must consider lead time of saftey stock and between when the order is placed and received; demand predictions; importance of the order, and inventory holding costs. Most of these explained is previous questions but the new one being importance of the order - a company essentially must prioritize orders between quantities, shipping to customers, customers expectancy etc. and conclude what orders are most important at that time being. Having the right amount of stock to meet demand is crucial but you don't want to fill orders that may not be due as soon, etc. which in turn can also be lead time. Lead time furthermore refers to when the order is placed and received. Clearly, all of these factors are each important and a business will need to consider one or more of them at all times.
